    "ttm The OHIO DAILY EXPRESS Published every Evening except Sunday by Paige H Strickland fet 1007 Germantown street Dayton 7 Ohio Phone HEmlock 1076 PAIGE H STRICKLAND Editor and Publisher RUBY L BLANKS Business Manager JNATIONAL ADVERTISING Interstate United Newspapers XC 545 Fifth Avenue New York 17 New York President Truman Estimates Over 000000 Necessary For Civil Rights Program in New Fiscal Year Budget WASHINGTON ANP In his 425 billion dollar budget pre sented to Congress last Monday President Truman asked that 125 billion dollars be used for dom estic programs of this amount he estimates that more than a mil lion dollars would be necessary to carry out his civil rights pro gram in the fiscal year beginning July 1 1950 These funds would be used for the expansion o the Civil Rights division of the Department of Justice and broader enforcement powers of the present civil rights laws and for the creation of an additional assistant attorney Gen eral to supervise this division Prom these funds would also be established a Fair employment Practices commision and a per manen Commission on Civil Rights The budget further proposed total funds of 21 billion dollars for social welfare health and"
